extractpak

This utility is derived from the original extractpak.c in timfel/monkey:

    https://github.com/timfel/monkey

The original repository describes extractpak and packpak as simple scripts for
working with Monkey Island Special Edition pak files. At the time this notice
was added, the repository listing showed extractpak.c, packpak.c, and readme.md,
but no LICENSE file.

Substantial local changes include:

- Command-line support for arbitrary pak filenames.
- Listing and debug modes.
- Output directory support.
- Robust handling for leading slash and empty archive paths.
- Non-fatal handling for per-file write failures.
- Correct filename table parsing for both Monkey Island Special Edition pak
  archives.
- Classic-only extraction for the embedded SCUMM data files.

The MIT License in this repository applies to the local modifications and
documentation. The original upstream code should be treated as having no
explicit license unless the upstream author publishes one.
